amajynmæ, æmæ sæm ʒævgar pajda cydī ūcy dæsniadæj</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>они были искусны строить башни, и благодаря этому мастерству им шли немалые заработки</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>they were skilled at building towers, and they received considerable earnings because of thanks this skill</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Čerm."/><biblScope>95</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>qæwy īw acærgægomaw ūs dæsny wydi</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>в ауле была одна пожилая женщина знахарка</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>there was one elderly healer woman in the aul</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Čerm."/><biblScope>176</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>dæw dær, mæ lymæn, dæsny nal ysʒæbæx kænʒæn</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>и тебя, приятель, не вылечит больше знахарь</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>and you, buddy, will no longer be cured by the healer</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>101</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>ʒorunmæ dæsni æj</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>говорить он мастер</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>he is a master at speaking</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Gurdž._Æduli"/><biblScope>77</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>fæcæj næ kizgæ dæsni ǧæwagæ</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>наша дочка нуждается в знахаре</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>our daughter needs a healer</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Gurdž._Æduli"/><biblScope>91</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>dæsny jæxīcæn næ zony</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>знахарь для себя не умеет (гадать)</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>the healer does not know how (to tell fortunes) for himself</q></cit><bibl><biblScope xml:lang="ru">поговорка</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">saying</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>rajsta ta dæsny Biganon aǧ˳yvzæ æmæ jæ ærtykkag xatt bīræ fezmæsta</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>взяла опять знахарка Биганон стакан и в третий раз долго в нем мешала</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>the healer Biganon took the glass again and for the third time stirred something in it for a long time</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Arsen"/><biblScope>41</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>су zonys dæsny ʒinadæj?</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>какое мастерство ты знаешь?</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>what skill do you know?</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>76</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>dæsnyʒinad k˳yrd k˳yndyl ах˳уr kæny</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>мастерству кузнец учится у кузнеца</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>the blacksmith learns the skills from the blacksmith</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III 200</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>xærdgæjæ dæsny</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>искусный (в вышивании) канителью</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>a good hand at needlework with gold twisted thread</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>57</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>dæsny wydysty mæsyg amajynmæ, æmæ sæm ʒævgar pajda cydī ūcy dæsniadæj</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>они были искусны строить башни, и благодаря этому мастерству им шли немалые заработки</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>they were skilled at building towers, and they received considerable earnings because of thanks this skill</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Čerm."/><biblScope>95</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>qæwy īw acærgægomaw ūs dæsny wydi</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>в ауле была одна пожилая женщина знахарка</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>there was one elderly healer woman in the aul</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Čerm."/><biblScope>176</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>dæw dær, mæ lymæn, dæsny nal ysʒæbæx kænʒæn</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>и тебя, приятель, не вылечит больше знахарь</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>and you, buddy, will no longer be cured by the healer</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>101</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>ʒorunmæ dæsni æj</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>говорить он мастер</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>he is a master at speaking</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Gurdž._Æduli"/><biblScope>77</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>fæcæj næ kizgæ dæsni ǧæwagæ</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>наша дочка нуждается в знахаре</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>our daughter needs a healer</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Gurdž._Æduli"/><biblScope>91</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>dæsny jæxīcæn næ zony</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>знахарь для себя не умеет (гадать)</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>the healer does not know how (to tell fortunes) for himself</q></cit><bibl><biblScope xml:lang="ru">поговорка</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">saying</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>rajsta ta dæsny Biganon aǧ˳yvzæ æmæ jæ ærtykkag xatt bīræ fezmæsta</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>взяла опять знахарка Биганон стакан и в третий раз долго в нем мешала</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>the healer Biganon took the glass again and for the third time stirred something in it for a long time</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Arsen"/><biblScope>41</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>су zonys dæsny ʒinadæj?</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>какое мастерство ты знаешь?</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>what skill do you know?</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>76</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>dæsnyʒinad k˳yrd k˳yndyl ах˳уr kæny</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>мастерству кузнец учится у кузнеца</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>the blacksmith learns the skills from the blacksmith</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III 200</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Отвечает <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>dakṣiṇa-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>dašina-</w></mentioned>. Основа *%ideks%i- выступает в индоевропейских языках в двух тесно связанных между собою значениях: с одной стороны, ‘правый’ (→ ‘правая рука’, ‘правая сторона’, ‘юг’), с другой — ‘искусный’, ‘удачный’, ‘благоприятный’ и пр. Известно, что ‘правая сторона’ с давних пор ассоциируется со счастьем, удачей, искусством, а ‘левая’ — с несчастьем, неудачей, неловкостью („правая рука“ = „искусная рука“). В осетинском значение ‘правый’, ‘правая рука’ отсутствует (см. <xr><ref target="#entry_raxīz"/></xr>). Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/><w>dašn</w><gloss><q>справа</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>δšny</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><gloss><q>благоприятный</q></gloss></mentioned> (а не „juste“, как переводит %sBenveniste%s: <bibl><ref target="#ref_TSP"/><biblScope>%i3%i 204</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>dašina-</w><gloss><q>правый</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>правая сторона</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>dakṣiṇa-</w><gloss><q>искусный</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>ловкий</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>правый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>правосторонний</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>южный</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>благоприятный</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/><w>деснъ</w><gloss><q>правый</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="cu"><w>десница</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/><w>desżinė́</w><gloss><q>правая рука</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/><w>δεξιός</w><gloss><q>искусный</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/><gloss><q>ловкий</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/><gloss><q>умный</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/><gloss><q>правый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/><gloss><q>справа находящийся</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/><gloss><q>благоприятный</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/><gloss><q>счастливый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w>δεξιότης</w><gloss><q>искусство</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/><gloss><q>мастерство</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (<mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/><w>dæsniad</w></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/><w>dexter</w><gloss><q>правый</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/><gloss><q>справа находящийся</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/><gloss><q>благоприятный</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/><gloss><q>приносящий счастье</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/><gloss><q>ловкий</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/><gloss><q>искусный</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w>dexteritas</w><gloss><q>ловкость</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/><gloss><q>искусство</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Для значения ‘знахарь’ ср. <mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/><w>usta</w><gloss><q>искусный</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><w/><gloss><q>знахарь</q></gloss></mentioned>, . <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>kṣ</w></mentioned> в осетинском отвечает обычно %ixs%i (см. <xr><ref target="#entry_rūxs"/></xr> ‘свет’, <xr><ref target="#entry_xsæv"/></xr> ‘ночь’, <xr><ref target="#entry_xsyr"/></xr> ‘молоко’ и др.); однако ср. <xr><ref target="#entry_syd"/></xr> ‘голод’ = <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>kṣudh-</w></mentioned>. %sВаilеу%s (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"/><biblScope>8</biblScope></bibl>) возводит %idæsny%i к *%idastya%i, что фонетически мало вероятно.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>47, 77, 82</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">It corresponds to <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>dakṣiṇa-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>dašina-</w></mentioned>. The stem *%ideks%i- has two closely related meanings in Indo-European languages: on the one hand, ‘right’ (→ ‘right hand’, ‘right side’, ‘south’), on the other — ‘skillfull’, ‘lucky’, ‘prosperous’ etc. It is known that ‘right side’ has been associated with happiness, luck, art for a long time and ‘left side’ — with misfortune, bad luck, awkwardness (“right hand” = “skilled hand”). The meaning ‘right’, ‘right side’ lacks in the Ossetic language (see <xr><ref target="#entry_raxīz"/></xr>). Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/><w>dašn</w><gloss><q>rightward</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>δšny</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><gloss><q>prosperous</q></gloss></mentioned> (and not “juste”, as translates %sBenveniste%s: <bibl><ref target="#ref_TSP"/><biblScope>%i3%i 204</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>dašina-</w><gloss><q>right</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>right side</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>dakṣiṇa-</w><gloss><q>skillfull</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>dexterous</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>right</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>right sided</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>southern</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>prosperous</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/><w>desnъ</w><gloss><q>right</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="cu"><w>desnitsa</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/><w>desżinė́</w><gloss><q>right hand</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/><w>δεξιός</w><gloss><q>skillfull</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/><gloss><q>dexterous</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/><gloss><q>clever</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/><gloss><q>right</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/><gloss><q>situated on the right</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/><gloss><q>prosperous</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/><gloss><q>happy</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w>δεξιότης</w><gloss><q>art</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/><gloss><q>skill</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (<mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/><w>dæsniad</w></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/><w>dexter</w><gloss><q>right</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/><gloss><q>situated on the right</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/><gloss><q>prosperous</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/><gloss><q>bringing happiness</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/><gloss><q>dexterous</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/><gloss><q>skillfull</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w>dexteritas</w><gloss><q>skill</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/><gloss><q>art</q></gloss></mentioned>, . For the meaning ‘healer’ cf. <mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/><w>usta</w><gloss><q>skillfull</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><w/><gloss><q>healer</q></gloss></mentioned>, . <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>kṣ</w></mentioned> usually refers to %ixs%i in Ossetic (see <xr><ref target="#entry_rūxs"/></xr> ‘light’, <xr><ref target="#entry_xsæv"/></xr> ‘night’, <xr><ref target="#entry_xsyr"/></xr> ‘milk’ etc.); however cf. <xr><ref target="#entry_syd"/></xr> ‘hunger’ = <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>kṣudh-</w></mentioned>. %sВаilеy%s (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"/><biblScope>8</biblScope></bibl>) traces %idæsny%i back to *%idastya%i, which is highly doubtful due to phonetic reasons.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>47, 77, 82</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry>